ulation in\nthis size range due to tidal disruption assuming that one $1\\km$ diameter NEO\ntidally disrupts at Earth every 2,500 years. These objects may be suitable\ntargets for asteroid retrieval missions due to their Earth-like orbits with\ncorresponding low $v_{\\infty}$. The fragments from the tidal disruptions at\nEarth have $\\sim5\\times$ the collision probability with Earth compared to the\nbackground NEO population.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 16 May 2014 08:31:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-19"}
